elements.title: Mirella Freni
elements.contents: ... that Mirella Freni (pictured) and Luciano Pavarotti, who co-starred as the lovers Mimì and Rodolfo in La bohème at La Scala in 1968, shared the same wet nurse?

elements.title: Bill Chisholm
elements.contents: ... that Bill Chisholm's announced $6.1 billion purchase of the Boston Celtics is the largest amount ever paid for a North American sports team?

elements.title: The Three Worlds of Evangelicalism
elements.contents: ... that a former management consultant who coined the framework of "The Three Worlds of Evangelicalism" was described by The New York Times as "a kind of Malcolm Gladwell of conservative Christianity"?

elements.title: Zug massacre
elements.contents: ... that the 2001 Zug massacre resulted in changes to security measures for public buildings, but not to Swiss gun laws?

elements.title: his blockbuster trade
elements.contents: ... that Juan Soto, before his blockbuster trade, rejected a 15-year, $440 million contract extension, which would have been the largest deal in Major League Baseball history at the time?

elements.title: heartburn
elements.contents: ... that about 25 percent of people experience heartburn at least once a month?

elements.title: Miroslav Kvočka
elements.contents: ... that Miroslav Kvočka was convicted of war crimes and crimes against humanity against non-Serb detainees in the Omarska concentration camp during the Bosnian War?

elements.title: Edmonds' Clock Tower
elements.contents: ... that the Edmonds' Clock Tower was split in two after the June 2011 Christchurch earthquakes?

elements.title: Juno
elements.contents: ... that the Overwatch character Juno was praised for her ability to reward players for having sound game sense?
